cs.DS, cs.CG, cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.LG. 

The paper deals with a graph optimization problem involving distances and weights, which suggests categories such as cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The use of exponential distributions and analysis of algorithms also points towards cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the mention of "almost linear time" hints at cs.LG (Machine Learning).
